//    private static final String SAMPLE_SUBLIST_ITEMS= "{\"query\":{\"pages\":{\"72759\":{\"pageid\":72759,\"ns\":0,\"title\":\"Accessory\",\"revisions\":[{\"*\":\"[[File:XC2-Accessories.png|thumb|250px|Accessories selection in inventory]]\\n'''Accessories''' (Japanese: {{lang|ja|\\u30a2\\u30af\\u30bb\\u30b5\\u30ea\\u30fc}}, ''Akusesar\\u012b'') are a type of equipment in ''[[Xenoblade Chronicles 2]]''. They are items worn by [[Driver]]s that strengthen them in various ways, from increasing maximum [[Hit Points (XC2)|HP]], to healing on criticals, or increasing resistance to debuffs such as [[Taunt (XC2)|Taunt]]. They can be purchased from Accessory [[Shop (XC2)|Shops]], received as enemy drops, crafted at special Shops, or received as rewards from [[Challenge Battle Mode]]. Compared to ''[[Xenoblade Chronicles]]'' and ''[[Xenoblade Chronicles X]]'', the Accessory mechanic somewhat works like a mix of both [[armour]]/[[armor]] and [[Gem]]s/[[Augment]]s mechanics.\\n\\nEach character owns two slots on which they can equip two different Accessories at a time, but they cannot have the same effect, for example both a [[Comet Choker]] and a [[Goddess Choker]] cannot be equipped because they both increase Luck by a percentage, while it is possible to wear the Comet Choker with a [[Gold Gear Choker]], which increases Luck by a fixed amount. \\n\\nIn [[New Game Plus (XC2)|New Game Plus]], [[Experience Points (XC2)#Bonus EXP|bonus EXP]] can be used at the [[Traveling Bard]] in the [[Argentum Trade Guild]] in exchange for an [[Accessory Expander Kit]], which grants a Driver a third accessory slot.\\n{{clr}}\\n\\n== Types of Accessories ==\\n{| align=\\\"center\\\" style=\\\"text-align:center;\\\"\\n| [[File:XC2-equipment-hat.png|96px]]\\n| [[File:XC2-equipment-gloves.png|96px]]\\n| [[File:XC2-equipment-vest.png|96px]]\\n| [[File:XC2-equipment-shoes.png|96px]]\\n| [[File:XC2-equipment-belt.png|96px]]\\n|-\\n| Hats\\n| Gloves\\n| Vests\\n| Shoes\\n| Belts\\n|-\\n| [[File:XC2-e